The above Janus/Deep Seek Group utilizes a safetensor version of Janus that can be found in the zip file you can download from: https://civitai.com/models/1191420/deepseek-janus-pro-1b-7b-safetensors

This is the only variant of Deep Seek that I've found that is utilizing a safetensor format, which is a bit safer to use than other variations. If you look at my Kitchensink series of workflows at https://openart.ai/workflows/profile/mongrel_monstrous_1?tab=workflows&sort=latest you may see some other llm variants that I've used to do descriptions/captions before other than Deep Seek.  However, I mainly use the Janus/Deepseek variant Janus Pro 1B listed above because it's a little faster than most other LLMs and is useful for generating captions. I DO NOT suggest using deep seek for actual image generation, only for captioning or describing the images in a specific folder in text files.  You can change the Image directory in the Batch Load Images (Mikey) node above to use whatever folder you have your images set up in.

The way I typically run this is right click group for above to bypass it and then use the flux group to generate a batch of images.  Then after that right click group to bypass the flux section and set this Janus group to always on (unbypassed) to read the folder of images I generated to create text descriptions of each image.  You can also aim it at whatever other folders you need to describe but I find it works best for the images generated in comfy since it has limits on pixel dimensions the images can be in.  

I also have an intermediate step if I'm not using the main flux image and only the one with footer where I use xnview to cut off footer before doing the Janus descriptions so that the footer won't be described in the Janus texts. I find it easier to do that sometimes for the descriptions since it makes it easier to upload images later. 

Images I personally am uploading using this technique can be found at https://payhip.com/buyart 

In olden days when ai first came out I used to use xnview to add footers, but find that adding footer here in comfyui is easier and makes more logical sense since the generated image keeps the workflow in the metadata.  On the https://payhip.com/buyart you can doanlost a lot of my images or purchase one. I used to try to make the workflows hidden in the buy only section but stopped doing that since it only makes sense for this type of technology to be shared in my opinion so others can make beautiful ai artwork too.  If you want to buy images there go ahead, if you want to just download images from there go ahead. If I upscale images, which I typically do for some of my favorites the upscaled version of those can be found at https://payhip.com/buyart/collection/upscaled upscaled variants are only for sale, but you may find some of the smaller non-upscaled variant of the same image with workflow available on the site too.  Eventually I may add some images to other sites and will try to link them from the main image pages at  https://payhip.com/buyart when I can, over time.  

Have fun.

6.19.25
ArsMJStyle, a beautiful scandinavian girl posing in the mountains, the sun is shining, the grass is green and flowers are everywhere

Openflux model and vae can be found at 
https://huggingface.co/ostris/OpenFLUX.1/tree/main

Flux Schnell model and vae can be found at https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-schnell/tree/main

You can also use other variants of flux with this workflow but I mainly use openflux, which is a non-distilled version of schnell. I perfer schnell over Dev because it's commercial use where as Dev is not.  Some have argued that Dev can be used commercially because the license states they make no claim over the output but other parts of the license for Dev state that it's mainly for non-commercial use so unless you are paying Black Forest for a commercial use license I find it safer to use actual commercial use licenses like we find in Schnell or Openflux variant.  

I also find it nicer hard drive space wise to only download and use models you really want to use, so I'm sticking with OpenFlux for now.  Eventually, if other things develop better like Auraflow it may make sense at that point to change models, but til then Open Flux can handle most stuff you throw at it and you are fairly safe using output from it commercially. Vae models go in the \ComfyUI\models\vae folder.

HAVE FUN!

06/19/2025

If you don't want to crop you don't have to. Use the bypassed Pad Image for Outpainting options above if you don't want to crop. I like cropping to help remove signatures sometimes.  A lot of the prompts I use are based on Public Domain art such as works by Frederic Remington and other artists that had unique signatures that would usually be put at the bottom of the image. I crop off a bit of the bottom and replace it with my blog's url footer to edit a bit of that out. It's not perfect but usually works.
